          "trust_score": 72.4,
          "opus_side": null,
          "thesis": "TCS has significantly exceeded its critical environmental target of reducing Scope 1 and Scope 2 emissions by 70% by 2025, achieving an 80% reduction (vs 2016 baseline) by FY2024. This demonstrates strong commitment and effective execution on sustainability goals, which are increasingly important for long-term value creation and stakeholder trust."
        },
        "WIPRO": {
          "trust_grade": "A",
          "trust_score": 83.7,
          "opus_side": null,
          "thesis": "**Operating margin resilience and cash generation durability.** Despite a flat full-year net profit growth of 0.36% YoY in FY26 (Mar 2026: 13,266 Cr vs Mar 2025: 13,218 Cr), Wipro has expanded operating margins from 20.2% in Mar 2025 to 19.2% in Mar 2026 (per Screener), and delivered 17.6% operating margin in Q3 FY26 at the high end of the 17-17.5% guided band. This is achieved despite HARMAN DTS integration (which management said would be 'margin-dilutive') and restructuring charges of INR 263 Cr in Q3. **Operating cash flow remained robust at 135% of net income in Q3 and 127.7% for full year FY26** (16,943 Cr OCF vs 13,266 Cr net profit), enabling the company to distribute >$1.3B in dividends (INR 11 per share equivalent) in FY26 while maintaining a gross cash position of $6.5B. This demonstrates **operational discipline and financial stability** even amid demand headwinds. The company is not sacrificing profitability or financial flexibility to chase revenue growth\u2014a disciplined stance that protects shareholder interests."
        },
        "BDL": {
          "trust_grade": "C",
          "trust_score": 56.8,
          "opus_side": null,
          "thesis": "BDL dramatically exceeded its GeM (Government e-Marketplace) procurement target, achieving \u20b95,841.7 Crore in GMV procurement against a \u20b91,602 Crore target in FY2023-24\u2014a 364.6% achievement rate. This demonstrates exceptional execution capability in government procurement processes and strong vendor ecosystem engagement. Additionally, the company exceeded its MSME procurement mandate, achieving 27.70% (\u20b9450.38 Crore) against a 25% statutory target, signalling both policy compliance and supply chain resilience (FY2023-24 AR, Directors' Report - Procurement from MSMEs, Page 16). These routine targets are delivered consistently, indicating reliable operational management at the tactical level."
        },
